paragraph.paragraph:
These conventions about letter case are only style rules.  Eiffel is case-insensitive, since it is foolish to assume that two identifiers denote two different things just on the basis of a letter written in lower or upper case.  The obvious exception is manifest character constants (appearing in single quotes, such as 

				'A'
			) and manifest character strings (appearing in double quotes, such as 

				"UPPER and lower"
			).
